{"title_page": "W36DO-D", "text_new": "{{Infobox broadcast\n| call_letters             = W36DO-D \n| city                     = Chicago, Illinois\n| station_logo             =  \n| station_branding         =  \n| station_slogan           =  \n| digital                  = 36 ([[ultra high frequency|UHF]])\n| virtual                  = 36 ([[Program and System Information Protocol|PSIP]]) \n| subchannels              = [[#Digital channels|(see below)]]\n| other_chs                = \n| affiliations             = [[#Digital channels|(see below)]] \n| location                 = [[Darby, Pennsylvania]]\n| country                  = [[United States]]\n| owner                    = [[HC2 Holdings]]\n| licensee                 = HC2 LPTV Holdings LLC\n| founded                  = 1990 \n| airdate                  = {{start date and age|1990|07|09|p=y}}  \n| callsign_meaning         =   \n| sister_stations          = \n| former_callsigns         = W55BT (1990-2008)\n| former_affiliations      =  \n| former_channel_numbers   = \n| effective_radiated_power = 1.2 [[Kilowatt|kW]] \n| HAAT                     = 272 ft\n| facility_id              = 72535\n| coordinates              = {{nowrap|{{coord|40|2|30.1|N|75|14|10.1|W|type:landmark_scale:2000}}}}   \n| licensing_authority      = [[Federal Communications Commission|FCC]]\n| homepage                 = \n}}\n\n'''W36DO-D''' is a [[Low-power broadcasting#Television|low-powered]] [[television station]] [[city of license|licensed]] to [[Darby, Pennsylvania]], [[United States]]. The station, which broadcasts its [[Digital terrestrial television|digital]] signal on [[virtual channel|virtual]] and [[ultra high frequency|UHF]] channel 36, is owned by [[HC2 Holdings]] and licensed to HC2 LPTV Holdings. The station is affiliated with [[Home Shopping Network|HSN]].<ref name=hc2>[https://www.rabbitears.info/market.php?request=print_station&facility_id=72535 Digital TV Market Listing for W36DO-D]</ref>\n\n==History== \nThe station\u2019s construction permit was issued on July 9, 1990 under the callsign of '''W55BT'''.  On June 11, 2008, it moved to the current callsign '''W36DO-D'''.<ref>http://www.fccinfo.com/CMDProEngine.php?sCurrentService=TV&tabSearchType=Appl&sAppIDNumber=72535</ref>\n\n==Digital channels==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! [[Digital subchannel#United States|Channel]]\n! [[Display resolution|Video]]\n! [[Aspect ratio (image)|Aspect]]\n! [[Program and System Information Protocol#What PSIP does|PSIP Short \nName]]\n! Programming<ref name=hc2/>\n|-\n| 36.1 \n| rowspan=4|[[480i]] \n| rowspan=4|[[16:9]] \n| rowspan=4|W36DO-D\n| [[Home Shopping Network|HSN]]\n|- \n| 36.2 \n| blank \n|- \n| 36.3 \n| [[Infomercial]]s\n|- \n| 36.4 \n| [[Azteca America]] \n|}\n\n\n==References== \n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{TVQ|W36DO-D}} \n\n{{Chicago TV}}\n{{HC2 Holdings}}\n\n[[Category:Digital low-power stations]]\n[[Category:HC2 Holdings]]\n[[Category:Television stations in Illinois]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 1990]]\n[[Category:1990 establishments in Illinois]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox broadcast\n| call_letters             = W36DO-D \n| city                     = Chicago, Illinois\n| station_logo             =  \n| station_branding         =  \n| station_slogan           =  \n| digital                  = 36 ([[ultra high frequency|UHF]])\n| virtual                  = 36 ([[Program and System Information Protocol|PSIP]]) \n| subchannels              = [[#Digital channels|(see below)]]\n| other_chs                = \n| affiliations             = [[#Digital channels|(see below)]] \n| location                 = [[Chicago, Illinois]]\n| country                  = [[United States]]\n| owner                    = [[HC2 Holdings]]\n| licensee                 = HC2 LPTV Holdings LLC\n| founded                  = 1990 \n| airdate                  = {{start date and age|1990|07|09|p=y}}  \n| callsign_meaning         =   \n| sister_stations          = \n| former_callsigns         = W55BT (1990-2008)\n| former_affiliations      =  \n| former_channel_numbers   = \n| effective_radiated_power = 1.2 [[Kilowatt|kW]] \n| HAAT                     = 272 ft\n| facility_id              = 72535\n| coordinates              = {{nowrap|{{coord|40|2|30.1|N|75|14|10.1|W|type:landmark_scale:2000}}}}   \n| licensing_authority      = [[Federal Communications Commission|FCC]]\n| homepage                 = \n}}\n\n'''W36DO-D''' is a [[Low-power broadcasting#Television|low-powered]] [[television station]] [[city of license|licensed]] to [[Chicago, Illinois]], [[United States]]. The station, which broadcasts its [[Digital terrestrial television|digital]] signal on [[virtual channel|virtual]] and [[ultra high frequency|UHF]] channel 36, is owned by [[HC2 Holdings]] and licensed to HC2 LPTV Holdings. The station is affiliated with [[Home Shopping Network|HSN]].<ref name=hc2>[https://www.rabbitears.info/market.php?request=print_station&facility_id=72535 Digital TV Market Listing for W36DO-D]</ref>\n\n==History== \nThe station\u2019s construction permit was issued on July 9, 1990 under the callsign of '''W55BT'''.  On June 11, 2008, it moved to the current callsign '''W36DO-D'''.<ref>http://www.fccinfo.com/CMDProEngine.php?sCurrentService=TV&tabSearchType=Appl&sAppIDNumber=72535</ref>\n\n==Digital channels==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! [[Digital subchannel#United States|Channel]]\n! [[Display resolution|Video]]\n! [[Aspect ratio (image)|Aspect]]\n! [[Program and System Information Protocol#What PSIP does|PSIP Short \nName]]\n! Programming<ref name=hc2/>\n|-\n| 36.1 \n| rowspan=4|[[480i]] \n| rowspan=4|[[16:9]] \n| rowspan=4|W36DO-D\n| [[Home Shopping Network|HSN]]\n|- \n| 36.2 \n| blank \n|- \n| 36.3 \n| [[Infomercial]]s\n|- \n| 36.4 \n| [[Azteca America]] \n|}\n\n\n==References== \n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{TVQ|W36DO-D}} \n\n{{Chicago TV}}\n{{HC2 Holdings}}\n\n[[Category:Digital low-power stations]]\n[[Category:HC2 Holdings]]\n[[Category:Television stations in Illinois]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 1990]]\n[[Category:1990 establishments in Illinois]]\n", "name_user": "Bumm13", "label": "safe", "comment": "changed two incorrect \"Chicago, Illinois\" wikilinks to correct \"Darby, Pennsylvania\"", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/W36DO-D"}
{"title_page": "Jason Hazeley", "text_new": "{{Merge|Joel Morris|discuss=Talk:Jason Hazeley#Proposed merge of Joel Morris with Jason Hazeley|date=April 2020}}\n'''Jason Hazeley''' is a British comedy writer. With long-time writing partner [[Joel Morris]], Hazeley has written many books,  and for many British comedy series, and films.\n\n==Early life==\nHazeley, whilst known as Jason Smith, attended [[King Edward VI Grammar School, Chelmsford|King Edward VI Grammar School]] in [[Chelmsford, Essex]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kegs.org.uk/notable-alumni/2647.html|title=Notable Alumni|website=www.kegs.org.uk}}</ref> which is where he met his later comedy partner [[Joel Morris]].<ref> https://www.inews.co.uk/culture/meet-men-invented-ladybird-books-grown-ups-not-millionaires-thousandaires-515348%3Famp </ref> Whilst at school they produced a parody newsletter, and at sixth form received their first paid work after selling a joke to the [[Russ Abbott]] show.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/radio/2018-01-10/ladybird-book-duo-joel-morris-and-jason-hazeley-are-now-spoofing-scandi-noir-on-radio-4/amp/|title=Ladybird Book duo Joel Morris and Jason Hazeley are now spoofing Scandi noir on Radio 4|website=Radio Times}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===Television and film===\nHazeley has written for a number of British TV shows and films. These include ''[[That Mitchell and Webb Look]]'', ''[[A Touch of Cloth]]'', [[Charlie Brooker]]'s ''[[Screenwipe]]'', ''Electionwipe'' and ''[[Newswipe]]'' programmes, and several [[Philomena Cunk]] series. The pair are regular contributors to the British adult comic ''[[Viz (comics)|Viz]]''. The 2016 Electionwipe won the [[BAFTA]] award for best Comedy and entertainment programme.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.bafta.org/television/comedy-comedy-entertainment-programme |title = Comedy & Comedy Entertainment Programme - CHARLIE BROOKer's 2016 WIPE|date = 11 April 2017}}</ref> They also wrote for [[Paddington (film)]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p06sbgbv|title=BBC Radio 2 - Jo Whiley & Simon Mayo, Jason Hazeley and Joel Morris, Ladybird Book Confession, The link between Ladybird, Paddington and Bins!|website=BBC}}</ref> and [[Paddington 2]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.unitedagents.co.uk/joel-morris-and-jason-hazeley|title=Joel Morris and Jason Hazeley &#124; United Agents|website=www.unitedagents.co.uk}}</ref>\n\n====Books====\nMorris and Hazeley have co-written books including ''[[Bollocks to Alton Towers]]'',<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=ughuyrUZZ1AC|title=Bollocks to Alton Towers: Uncommonly British Days Out|first1=Jason|last1=Hazeley|first2=Robin|last2=Halstead|first3=Alex|last3=Morris|first4=Joel|last4=Morris|date=March 2, 2006|publisher=Penguin Adult|isbn=9780141021201|via=Google Books}}</ref> and a series of parody [[Ladybird books]] which re-caption original illustrations from the Ladybird series with jokes aimed at an adult audience.<ref name=\"BBC News 12 October 2015\">{{cite web | title= Spoof Ladybird books target adult market |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-34503866| author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->|date= 12 October 2015| website= [[BBC News Online]] | accessdate= 12 October 2015}}</ref> Topics have included [[Donald Trump]],<ref> https://www.inews.co.uk/culture/books/jason-hazeley-joel-morris-a-ladybird-book-about-trump-interview-release-638826%3Famp</ref> hipsters and hangovers<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.irishtimes.com/culture/books/ladybird-books-mid-life-crisis-new-books-take-on-hangovers-and-hipsters-1.2388551?mode=amp | title=Ladybird Books' mid-life crisis: New books take on hangovers and hipsters}}</ref> and [[Brexit]].<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2018/oct/25/ladybird-book-authors-make-light-work-of-brexit |title = Ladybird book authors make light work of Brexit|newspaper = The Guardian|date = 25 October 2018}}</ref> The books were so successful that in 2015 only [[JK Rowling]], [[David Walliams]] and [[Julia Donaldson]] sold more copies in the UK.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/men/thinking-man/meet-the-ladybird-authors-knocking-everyone-off-the-best-sellers/amp/ |title = Meet the Ladybird authors knocking everyone off the best-sellers list - including me}}</ref>\n\n====Podcast====\nThey also host the comedy podcast ''Rule of Three''.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sawyer |first1=Miranda |title=The week in radio and podcasts: Football Daily; Giant; Athletico Mince |url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2019/jun/23/radio-podcasts-football-daily-giant-athletico-mince-reviews |accessdate=6 April 2020 |work=The Observer |date=23 June 2019}}</ref>\nRule of Three was named in the best podcasts of 2018 by The Guardian.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2018/jun/30/the-50-best-podcasts-of-2018|title=The 50 best podcasts of 2018|first1=Hannah J.|last1=Davies|first2=Hannah|last2=Verdier|first3=Harriet|last3=Gibsone|first4=Gavin|last4=Haynes|date=June 30, 2018|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref> On the show they invite a comedy performer on to discuss their career and a comedy performance or programme, a TV show, a film, a book, an album or a comic that means a lot to them.<ref> https://www.podnews.net/podcast/1362621695</ref> Guests have included [[Eddie Izzard]], [[John Finnemore]], [[Danielle Ward]], [[Jon Holmes]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wearecult.rocks/podcast-of-the-week-rule-of-three|title=Podcast of the Week: Rule Of Three \u00bb We Are Cult|first=James|last=Gent|date=June 8, 2018}}</ref> and[[Aisling Bea]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aislingbea.com/podcasts/rule-of-three/|title=AISLING BEA - Actor, Writer, Stand-Up, MC. People have woken up to worse. Rule Of Three \u2013 Father Ted|first=Aisling|last=Bea|website=www.aislingbea.com}}</ref> Topics have included [[Bill Hicks]], films such as [[Trading Places]] and [[Time Bandits]] and the  LP version of ''[[The Album of the Soundtrack of the Trailer of the Film of Monty Python and the Holy Grail]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rnz.co.nz/national/programmes/the-podcast-hour/audio/2018660535/dissecting-comedy-classics-rule-of-three|title=Dissecting comedy classics: Rule of Three|date=August 31, 2018|website=RNZ}}</ref> The podcast has branched out into live shows with special guests such as [[Sue Perkins]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kingsplace.co.uk/whats-on/comedy/rule-of-three/|title=Rule of Three with special guest Sue Perkins \u2022 Comedy \u2022 Kings Place|website=Kings Place}}</ref> Hazeley has also appeared as a guest on the Griefcast podcast with [[Cariad Lloyd]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.listennotes.com/podcasts/griefcast/ep-56-jason-hazeley-UE_BT-9saO5/|title=Ep. 56 Jason Hazeley - Griefcast (podcast)|website=Listen Notes}}</ref>\n\n====Music====\nFrom 1998 to 2003 Hazeley was part of the folk-pop duo [[Ben & Jason]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/artists/71f13beb-f273-4af4-8154-a1c21c496dc3|title=Ben & Jason - New Songs, Playlists & Latest News - BBC Music|website=BBC}}</ref>\n\n==Publications==\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |authorlink1=Jason Hazeley |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |title=How it Works: The Husband |date=29 October 2015 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8356-1 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=How it Works: The Wife |date=29 October 2015 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8354-7 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of Dating |date=29 October 2015 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8357-8 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of Mindfulness |date=29 October 2015 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8352-3 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of The Hangover |date=29 October 2015 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8351-6 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of The Hipster |date=29 October 2015 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8359-2 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of The Mid-Life Crisis |date=29 October 2015 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8353-0 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of The Shed |date=29 October 2015 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8358-5 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=How it Works: The Mum |date=11 February 2016 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8421-6 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=How it Works: The Dad |date=19 May 2016 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8426-1 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=How it Works: The Student |date=25 August 2016 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8428-5 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=How it Works: The Cat |date=20 October 2016 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8433-9 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=How it Works: The Dog |date=20 October 2016 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8435-3 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=How it Works: The Grandparent |date=20 October 2016 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8430-8 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of Red Tape |date=20 October 2016 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8439-1 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of The Meeting |date=20 October 2016 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8437-7 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of The People Next Door |date=20 October 2016 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8441-4 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of The Sickie |date=20 October 2016 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8443-8 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of The Zombie Apocalypse |date=20 October 2016 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8445-2 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of Boxing Day |date=1 December 2016 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8486-5 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of The Do-Gooder |date=23 February 2017 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8447-6 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=How it Works: The Baby |date=5 October 2017 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8863-4 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=How it Works: The Brother |date=5 October 2017 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8869-6 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=How it Works: The Sister |date=5 October 2017 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8870-2 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=People at Work: The Rock Star |date=5 October 2017 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8865-8 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of Balls |date=5 October 2017 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8871-9 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of The Big Night Out |date=5 October 2017 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8867-2 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of The Ex |date=5 October 2017 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8866-5 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of The Nerd |date=5 October 2017 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8864-1 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of The New You |date=5 October 2017 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8885-6 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of The Quiet Night In |date=5 October 2017 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8868-9 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=A Ladybird First Grown-Up Picture Book |date=5 October 2017 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8884-9 }}\n\n==See also==\n*''[[Bollocks to Alton Towers]]'' ({{ISBN|0-14-102120-9}})\n*''[[More Bollocks to Alton Towers]]'' ({{ISBN|0-14-102785-1}})\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hazeley, Jason}}\n[[Category:British comedy writers]]\n[[Category:British male singers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{UK-writer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Merge|Joel Morris|discuss=Talk:Jason Hazeley#Proposed merge of Joel Morris with Jason Hazeley|date=April 2020}}\n'''Jason Hazeley''' is a British comedy writer. With long-time writing partner [[Joel Morris]], Hazeley has written many books,  and for many British comedy series, and films.\n\n==Early life==\nHazeley, whilst known as Jason Smith, attended [[King Edward VI Grammar School]] in [[Chelmsford, Essex]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kegs.org.uk/notable-alumni/2647.html|title=Notable Alumni|website=www.kegs.org.uk}}</ref> which is where he met his later comedy partner [[Joel Morris]].<ref> https://www.inews.co.uk/culture/meet-men-invented-ladybird-books-grown-ups-not-millionaires-thousandaires-515348%3Famp </ref> Whilst at school they produced a parody newsletter, and at sixth form received their first paid work after selling a joke to the [[Russ Abbott]] show.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.radiotimes.com/news/radio/2018-01-10/ladybird-book-duo-joel-morris-and-jason-hazeley-are-now-spoofing-scandi-noir-on-radio-4/amp/|title=Ladybird Book duo Joel Morris and Jason Hazeley are now spoofing Scandi noir on Radio 4|website=Radio Times}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===Television and film===\nHazeley has written for a number of British TV shows and films. These include  ''[[Philomena Cunk]], ''[[That Mitchell and Webb Look]]'' ''[[A Touch of Cloth]]'', and [[Charlie Brooker]]'s ''[[Screenwipe]]'', ''Electionwipe'' and ''[[Newswipe]]'' programmes, and the pair are regular contributors to the British adult comic ''[[Viz (comics)|Viz]]''. The 2016 Electionwipe won the [[BAFTA]] award for best Comedy and entertainment programme.<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.bafta.org/television/comedy-comedy-entertainment-programme |title = Comedy & Comedy Entertainment Programme - CHARLIE BROOKer's 2016 WIPE|date = 11 April 2017}}</ref> They also wrote for [[Paddington (film)]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p06sbgbv|title=BBC Radio 2 - Jo Whiley & Simon Mayo, Jason Hazeley and Joel Morris, Ladybird Book Confession, The link between Ladybird, Paddington and Bins!|website=BBC}}</ref> and [[Paddington 2]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unitedagents.co.uk/joel-morris-and-jason-hazeley|title=Joel Morris and Jason Hazeley &#124; United Agents|website=www.unitedagents.co.uk}}</ref>\n\n====Books====\nMorris and Hazeley have co-written books including ''[[Bollocks to Alton Towers]]'',<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/?id=ughuyrUZZ1AC|title=Bollocks to Alton Towers: Uncommonly British Days Out|first1=Jason|last1=Hazeley|first2=Robin|last2=Halstead|first3=Alex|last3=Morris|first4=Joel|last4=Morris|date=March 2, 2006|publisher=Penguin Adult|isbn=9780141021201|via=Google Books}}</ref> and a series of parody [[Ladybird books]] which re-caption original illustrations from the Ladybird series with jokes aimed at an adult audience.<ref name=\"BBC News 12 October 2015\">{{cite web | title= Spoof Ladybird books target adult market |url= https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-34503866| author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.-->|date= 12 October 2015| website= [[BBC News Online]] | accessdate= 12 October 2015}}</ref> Topics have included [[Donald Trump]]<ref> https://www.inews.co.uk/culture/books/jason-hazeley-joel-morris-a-ladybird-book-about-trump-interview-release-638826%3Famp</ref>, hipsters and hangovers<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.irishtimes.com/culture/books/ladybird-books-mid-life-crisis-new-books-take-on-hangovers-and-hipsters-1.2388551?mode=amp | title=Ladybird Books' mid-life crisis: New books take on hangovers and hipsters}}</ref> and [[Brexit]].<ref>{{Cite news | url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2018/oct/25/ladybird-book-authors-make-light-work-of-brexit |title = Ladybird book authors make light work of Brexit|newspaper = The Guardian|date = 25 October 2018}}</ref> The books were so successful that in 2015 only [[JK Rowling]], [[David Walliams]] and [[Julia Donaldson]] sold more copies in the UK.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/men/thinking-man/meet-the-ladybird-authors-knocking-everyone-off-the-best-sellers/amp/ |title = Meet the Ladybird authors knocking everyone off the best-sellers list - including me}}</ref>\n\n====Podcast====\nThey also host the comedy podcast ''Rule of Three''.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sawyer |first1=Miranda |title=The week in radio and podcasts: Football Daily; Giant; Athletico Mince |url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2019/jun/23/radio-podcasts-football-daily-giant-athletico-mince-reviews |accessdate=6 April 2020 |work=The Observer |date=23 June 2019}}</ref>\nRule of Three was named in the best podcasts of 2018 by The Guardian.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2018/jun/30/the-50-best-podcasts-of-2018|title=The 50 best podcasts of 2018|first1=Hannah J.|last1=Davies|first2=Hannah|last2=Verdier|first3=Harriet|last3=Gibsone|first4=Gavin|last4=Haynes|date=June 30, 2018|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref> On the show they invite a comedy performer on to discuss their career and a comedy performance or programme, a TV show, a film, a book, an album or a comic that means a lot to them.<ref> https://www.podnews.net/podcast/1362621695</ref> Guests have included [[Eddie Izzard]], [[John Finnemore]], [[Danielle Ward]], [[Jon Holmes]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://wearecult.rocks/podcast-of-the-week-rule-of-three|title=Podcast of the Week: Rule Of Three \u00bb We Are Cult|first=James|last=Gent|date=June 8, 2018}}</ref>, and[[Aisling Bea]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aislingbea.com/podcasts/rule-of-three/|title=AISLING BEA - Actor, Writer, Stand-Up, MC. People have woken up to worse. Rule Of Three \u2013 Father Ted|first=Aisling|last=Bea|website=www.aislingbea.com}}</ref> Topics have included [[Bill Hicks]], films such as [[Trading Places]] and [[Time Bandits]] and the  LP version of ''[[The Album of the Soundtrack of the Trailer of the Film of Monty Python and the Holy Grail]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rnz.co.nz/national/programmes/the-podcast-hour/audio/2018660535/dissecting-comedy-classics-rule-of-three|title=Dissecting comedy classics: Rule of Three|date=August 31, 2018|website=RNZ}}</ref> The podcast has branched out into live shows with special guests such as [[Sue Perkins]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kingsplace.co.uk/whats-on/comedy/rule-of-three/|title=Rule of Three with special guest Sue Perkins \u2022 Comedy \u2022 Kings Place|website=Kings Place}}</ref> Hazeley has also appeared as a guest on the Griefcast podcast with [[Cariad Lloyd]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.listennotes.com/podcasts/griefcast/ep-56-jason-hazeley-UE_BT-9saO5/|title=Ep. 56 Jason Hazeley - Griefcast (podcast)|website=Listen Notes}}</ref>\n\n====Music====\nFrom 1998 to 2003 Hazeley was part of the folk-pop duo [[Ben & Jason]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/music/artists/71f13beb-f273-4af4-8154-a1c21c496dc3|title=Ben & Jason - New Songs, Playlists & Latest News - BBC Music|website=BBC}}</ref>\n\n==Publications==\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |authorlink1=Jason Hazeley |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |title=How it Works: The Husband |date=29 October 2015 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8356-1 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=How it Works: The Wife |date=29 October 2015 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8354-7 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of Dating |date=29 October 2015 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8357-8 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of Mindfulness |date=29 October 2015 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8352-3 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of The Hangover |date=29 October 2015 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8351-6 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of The Hipster |date=29 October 2015 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8359-2 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of The Mid-Life Crisis |date=29 October 2015 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8353-0 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=The Ladybird Book of The Shed |date=29 October 2015 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=Loughborough |isbn=978-0-7181-8358-5 }}\n*{{cite book |last1=Hazeley |first1=Jason A. |last2=Morris |first2=Joel P. |authormask1=2 |title=How it Works: The Mum |date=11 February 2016 |publisher=[[Ladybird Books]] |location=