{"title_page": "Tarik Filipovi\u0107", "text_new": "{{short description|Bosnian and Croatian television presenter and actor}}\n{{BLP more footnotes|date=October 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Tarik Filipovi\u0107\n| image       = \n| alt         = \n| caption     = \n| birth_name =  \n| birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|1972|3|11|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Zenica]], [[Socialist Republic of Bosnia and Herzegovina|SR Bosnia and Herzegovina]], [[SFR Yugoslavia]]\n| nationality = [[Bosnians|Bosnian]] <br> [[Bosniaks of Croatia|Croatian]] \n| spouse = Lejla \u0160ehovi\u0107\n| occupation  = {{hlist|TV presenter|actor}} \n}}\n\n'''Tarik Filipovi\u0107''' (born 11 March 1972) is a [[Bosnians|Bosnian]] and [[Bosniaks of Croatia|Croatian]] television presenter and actor. He has appeared in over 800 theatre plays since his debut in 1985. He has also been in many films and TV dramas produced throughout the areas of former [[Yugoslavia]].\n\nHe presents quiz shows ''Tko \u017eeli biti milijuna\u0161?'' (Croatia's ''[[Who Wants to Be a Millionaire?]]'') on [[Croatian Radiotelevision]], and ''Potjera'' ([[Croatia]]'s ''[[The Chase (UK game show)|The Chase]]'') on [[HRT 1|HRT1]]. In 2001, Filipovi\u0107 starred in ''[[Behind Enemy Lines (2001 film)|Behind Enemy Lines]]'' as a Serbian soldier.\n\n==Personal life==\nFilipovi\u0107 is married to Lejla \u0160ehovi\u0107 with whom he has two sons, Dino and Arman. He is also a supporter of [[NK \u010celik Zenica]] and is a member of the club's administration.\n\nApart from \u010celik, he is an avid supporter of [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb]] and is known for helping Dinamo Zagreb supporters from the [[Dubrava, Zagreb|Dubrava]] neighbourhood in several tight situations.{{citation needed|date=October 2016}}\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1993\n| ''Okus limuna''\n|\n| Croatian film\n|-\n| 1994\n| ''[[The Price of Life (1994 film)|The Price of Life]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| 1995\n| ''[[Washed Out (film)|Washed Out]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n| 1998\n| ''[[Agonija]]''\n| Inspector\n| Croatian film\n|-\n| 2000\n| ''Srce nije u modi''\n| Hrvatski Vojnik\n|\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''Polagana predaja''\n|\n|\n|-\n| 2001\n| ''[[Behind Enemy Lines (2001 film)|2001]]''\n| Serbian soldier\n|\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[24 Hours (2002 film)|24 Hours]]''\n| \u017duti\n|\n|-\n| 2003\n| ''[[Witnesses (2003 film)|Witnesses]]''\n| Javni tu\u017eitelj\n|\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Long Dark Night]]''\n| Joka\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=4|2005\n| ''[[First Class Thieves]]''\n| Narrator\n| Voice\n|-\n| ''[[Two Players from the Bench]]''\n| Anti\u0161a\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Go West (2005 film)|Go West]]''\n| Milan\n| Acting together with [[Rade \u0160erbed\u017eija]]\n|-\n| ''Dobro u\u0161timani mrtvaci''\n| Mario\n|\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Ice Age: The Meltdown]]''\n| Diego\n| Uncredited\n|-\n| 2007\n| ''Ritam \u017eivota''\n| Damir\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2009\n| ''[[Storm (2009 film)|Storm]]''\n| Mladen Banovic\n|\n|-\n| ''U zemlji cudesa''\n| Profesor\n|\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Ice Age: Continental Drift]]''\n| Diego\n| Voice\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2014\n| ''Devet polo\u017eaja samo\u0107e''\n|\n|\n|-\n| ''Markov trg''\n| Marko Crnoga\u010da\n| TV movie\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[ZG80]]''\n| Policeman from train #1\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''General''\n| Davor Domazet Lo\u0161o\n|\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''Smogovci''\n| Spasoje\n| Croatian TV-series\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Na\u0161i i va\u0161i]]''\n| prosjak-voditelj\n| 1 episode\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Na\u0161a mala klinika]]''\n| Harald Schmidt\n| 1 episode\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[A Mess in the House]]''\n| Tarik Filipovi\u0107\n| 1 episode (acting himself)\n|-\n| 2005\u20132010\n| ''[[Bitange i princeze]]''\n| Teodor \"Teo\" Fri\u0161\u010di\u0107\n|\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''Ljubav, navika, panika''\n| Damir\n| 1 episode\n|-\n| 2006\u20132007\n| ''Kazali\u0161te u ku\u0107i''\